Well, It took longer than I thought, but I finally hooked my brother on EQ yesterday /grins evilly<br>
<br>
He started....yup...a Wizard!<br>
<br>
So my scenario is this....I have my 62 and climbing wizard but I'm gonna start a level 1 toon to play with a bit. It would be one thing if I was on a 3rd account, then I'd start a cleric to rez my Wizard with =)<br>
<br>
Since I'm on my own account I guess I have to just play something fun. I was considering a SK since i have some gear already but I'm open to suggestions.<br>
<br>
Do you think Wizard SK would be an ok combo? Probably not one of the better combo's imo. Maybe a /gulp druid? No I'd have to smack myself daily if I made a dr00d. Bard perhaps? I don't know......what's fun?<br>
<br>
Nuuk Sfortenk<br>
