Champions in Arms <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543402</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=murel>Murel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1592<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 1:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> At low levels, I always really wanted a tank to hold off the mobs while I nuked. Back when root drained too much mana and never stuck for long anyway. <br>
<br>
I think an SK would be an awesome partner for a wizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tessei>Tessei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 2:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> Other good combos for a wiz are necro (fear kite and wiz doesnt have to worry about agro) and an enchanter (could pet tank/charm kill/fear kite and would always have breeze/clarity with you). <br>
I played with a necro before all the fear pathing changes, and it worked VERY well. <br>
<br>
You can try a wiz/cleric combo, its ok, mainly root/nuke, faster and better with undead. Can quad it takes some practice but is doable, the hard part is the wizard must maintain agro on mobs when cleric PBAE's them.<br>
<br>
But alot depends on what you want to focus on, group or just duo imo. If you want to duo pick a necro, if you want to group later pick a cleric, maybe a shaman (could duo with a shaman but would only have to pet tank) or the enchanter so that way you can get pick up groups. I cant tell you the number of groups I have gotten only b/c my gf is a cleric and she gets the invite. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Where government is afraid of the people there is freedom. Where the people are afraid of the government there is tyranny&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->--<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Thomas Jefferson</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lascarisgalasanameldo>Lascaris GalasAnameldo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 2:08 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> Try a beastlord.  I've played quite a few characters (63 wiz, 55 beastlord, 53 pally, 45 sk, 40 cleric, 30 warrior, 24 mage, 24 necro, a few others) and of all of them I think a Beast would be one of the better matches to go with a wizard.  One of the biggest drawbacks to beastlords is no snare/root, wiz can do that.  Beasts can pet cleric, jumping in and out to tank, have mana/hp regen, decent buffs, slow (and haste at lvl 60) and with the pet have very reasonable dps.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=289878">Lascaris - 63 Wizard,</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=456699"> Tomus - 53 Paladin of Brell </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corinia>Corinia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 3:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> My two experiences are wizard/mage and wizard/paladin.  This is from two different servers.  I played the wiz both times and my brother was a mage on one and a pally on the other.  I like both combos.<br>
<br>
I'm pretty used to the pally now and would suggest that.  For one, you can rez the pally when he dies saving the wizzies butt and for two you can rez the wizard when you fail to save his butt.  Pally makes an awesome tank.  Heals are nice.  Wizard nuke back up is great.  I suggest the deepwater helm when you get to that level for the free heals.  My bro still uses it at times.  Develop the stun and blind line.  It's excellent for regaining aggro from the wizzy if he nukes too soon.  Keep the undead spells up.  You can have fun killing undead anywhere and wizzy can join.  There are some places where the wizard will find he gets better exp than the pally and vice versa.<br>
<br>
It's been awhile since I did the mage/wizzy combo but as I recall, that was fun too and I have no problems grouping with a mage. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.questorsmoy.com/eqmemberinfopages/storyrenia/reniasig3.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artillis>Artillis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Enjoys Sheep Erotica</span><br>  Posts: 1961<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 3:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> I'd make an enchanter on anouther acount in a heartbeat just so I could have free KEI at my beck and call after I got them to level 60.  <br>
<br>
Constant KEI when you want it is &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; then all.<br>
<br>
No I'm not a KEI addict (*twitches*). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=onnatop>Onnatop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 560<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 3:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> I've heard many good things about BSTs and their ability to solo, I would imagine a BST/WIZ combo would be pretty damn good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solarax6975>solarax6975</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 462<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 6:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> i hear bst is good but man i love playing a monk atm<br>
