<br>
I know I know, friends don't let friends make ranger but hey, he's your brother. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadiar>Nadiar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Mistyr Smartipants</span><br>  Posts: 1358<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 6:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> Unless you just want to duo forever, start a bard.<br>
<br>
Bards add a ton to a group, so they can usually find one pretty easily.<br>
<br>
Once he reaches the 30's and can quadkite, you should be able to run near the mobs and pbae DoT them, which means anything he can keep snared and aggrod is fair game.<br>
<br>
And do you know what the best part about bards is? If he decides to switch classes, every class in the game works well with a bard (although a warrior may be slow). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saradin>Saradin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>South Mantis</span><br>  Posts: 2481<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 9:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class should I make?</span><hr size=1> bah, Rangers are great. Don't forget they can track the nameds too. Though maybe not nearly as profitable today as it used to be before PoP but still quite the worthy addition.<br>
<br>
Though I have to agree with Nadiar on the Bard. They can Fear kite too so that renders Necro pluses down to nill. They can snare (saves the Wizard mana), mana song, etc... Fook, no wonder they always broken. They got more tools than Sears. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><br>
